# Project Overview

-   Describe probability as a foundation of statistical modeling, including inference and maximum likelihood estimation
-   Determine and apply the appropriate generalized linear model for a specific data context Conduct model selection for a set of candidate models
-   Communicate the results of statistical models to a general audience Use programming software (i.e., R) to fit and assess statistical models

Here is my final project for Stats 631: Statistical Modeling and Regression

**goal**: use the data set below to predict inventory for the following year

**limitations**: For time series predictions it is best to use a data set that can be trended over multiple years. The data below only include 54 weeks of data

**this report contains:**

-   an exploratory analysis and descriptive analytics
-   feature engineering
-   step-wise model selection
-   splitting data into test and train sets and models
-   interpretation and evaluation the results

## Initial Insights:

The initial inventory data set contains 488 items sold over the course of 54 weeks (0-53), with a total of \~ 1.3 million units sold.


::: {.cell}

